subproject.description:
The overall scope of the programme is support for:
(i) Strategic planning; (ii) Capacity building and skills transfer; (iii) Knowledge management; and (iv) Monitoring and evaluation, including the domestication of MDGs within the health sector.
It will be achieved through the implementation of the following sub programmes: (i) Health Professionals Volunteerism and Capacity Development Programme; (ii) Health Planning Support Programme; (iii) Knowledge Management and Leadership Development Programme; and (iv) MDGs, Monitoring and Evaluation System. 
The following results are expected at the end of the programme: (i) Increased retention rate of Health Professionals and interns in the Province; (ii) Improved quality and quantity of health care service delivery in the Province; (iii) Increased appreciation of volunteerism and a commitment of local Health Professionals and Allied Health Professionals to serve in Limpopo; (iv) Improved use of information for planning, monitoring and evaluation; and (v) Increased capacity to conduct monitoring and evaluation
subproject.title: UNDP Support to the Health Sec
